"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-news-news-world-france-bids-reluctant-farewell-to-dazzling-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbNews\\u00bbWorld  ByAgence France Presse  6 minute read  13 August 2024  03:00 am  France's President Emmanuel Macron holds an Olympic gold medal manufactured by La Monnaie de Paris as he delivers a speech during a meeting with representatives of stakeholders who contributed to the organising and hosting of the 2024 Paris Olympic Games, at the Elysee presidential Palace in Paris, on August 12, 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 88, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Monnaie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Monnaie\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q24354\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Monnaie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Monnaie\"}, {\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594330107958015e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594330107958015e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by Benoit Tessier / POOL / AFP)  France bid a reluctant farewell on Monday to an \\\"enchanted\\\" fortnight of Olympic sport as athletes headed home from Paris praising a dazzling edition of the Games that has breathed new life into the biggest show on earth.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 412, \"end\": 418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"score\": 0.9999996007319056, \"rank\": 3.992673532524326e-07, \"text\": \"Benoit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\"}, {\"begin\": 442, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594330107958015e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hollywood star Tom Cruise delivered stardust at the closing ceremony on Sunday evening - and a link with the next Games in Los Angeles - by abseiling into the national stadium.\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.562161413647912e-14, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.285574546690083e-14, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"Mission Impossible\\\" star descended on a wire in front of 71,500 spectators, grabbed the Olympic flag and jumped onto a motorbike, to\\u00a0the delight of thousands of dancing athletes and awe-struck fans.\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The final act of the Paris Olympics brought relief that an event foreshadowed by worries about terror attacks, strikes or protests had passed off with barely a hitch.\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there was also sadness that two weeks of high-spirited celebration had come to an end.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:France youth rugby player 'swept away' by wave in Cape Town  \\\"Keep the flame alive,\\\" urged the front-page headline of France's biggest sports newspaper, L'Equipe, which featured new national swimming hero Leon Marchand and urged French people to maintain the spirit \\\"of this enchanted fortnight\\\".\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1436, \"end\": 1442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1528, \"end\": 1536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9847941014730888, \"rank\": 0.0150659079613769, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Athletes' Village in northern Paris, bleary-eyed athletes were packing their bags after a late night, with the French capital's two main airports braced for a huge influx of travellers and sports equipment.\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594330107958015e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8798530230141854, \"rank\": 0.12684215613358735, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Magda Skarbonkiewicz, a Team USA fencer, said she would return home filled with memories of competing inside the Grand Palais, one of the historic venues used around the French capital.\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bond_girl\", \"score\": 0.9999999861838661, \"rank\": 1.3816226388062067e-08, \"text\": \"Magda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bond_girl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bond_girl\"}, {\"begin\": 1855, \"end\": 1863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.6848205492541449, \"rank\": 0.46023001919058815, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2001, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8798530230141854, \"rank\": 0.12684215613358735, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's such an iconic venue and just nothing like I have ever seen before,\\\" she told AFP.\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2102, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.102072303107443e-27, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's amazing to see so many people care about fencing the way the French people do.\\\"\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During Sunday night's closing ceremony, which stressed the Olympics' core message of peace and cooperation, International Olympic Committee (IOC) president Thomas Bach had praised the Paris Games for being \\\"sport at its best\\\".\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2302, \"end\": 2339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:France tells nationals visiting Iran to leave 'as soon as possible'  \\\"These were sensational Olympic Games from start to finish,\\\" Bach said.\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2432, \"end\": 2438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2464, \"end\": 2468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.8147211222659814, \"rank\": 0.2273512819346841, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 2562, \"end\": 2566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4914763653306997e-22, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Or dare I say: Seine-sational Games,\\\" the IOC chief quipped in a pun about the river flowing through Paris which was a sometimes fickle star of the event.\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2616, \"end\": 2619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2567430178764534e-41, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2675, \"end\": 2680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594330107958015e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Observers had seen Paris 2024 as essential for the Olympics brand as a whole, coming after a Covid-affected edition in Tokyo and a corruption-tainted version in Rio de Janeiro in 2016.\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2749, \"end\": 2759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0252120968730198e-33, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2849, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998661029368441, \"rank\": 0.00013391499348805835, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1248218453171397e-25, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 9,000 athletes flooded into the Stade de France on Sunday night for a show that featured music from French electro act Air, guitar band Phoenix, Belgian singer Angele and the Cambodian rapper VannDa.\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 3122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3023, \"end\": 3029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8798530230141854, \"rank\": 0.12684215613358735, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3059, \"end\": 3066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Suns\", \"score\": 0.9614032015208521, \"rank\": 0.040146313119830274, \"text\": \"Phoenix\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Suns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Suns\"}, {\"begin\": 3068, \"end\": 3075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999928837376869, \"rank\": 7.116301546529734e-06, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 3098, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cambodia\", \"score\": 0.9999077978353789, \"rank\": 8.751130343644175e-05, \"text\": \"Cambodian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cambodia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cambodia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We knew you would be brilliant, but you were magic,\\\" Paris 2024 organising chief Tony Estanguet told the crowd during a triumphalist speech.\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3206, \"end\": 3220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said the Games had transformed \\\"a nation of implacable complainers\\\" into \\\"unbridled supporters who do not want to stop singing\\\".\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:Fibre optic cables targeted in new infrastructure attack in France  Much of the media commentary has focused on the uplifting impact of the Games on the generally morose national mood.\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3470, \"end\": 3476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999993280646305, \"rank\": 6.717924029786129e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just weeks before the Olympics, snap elections called by President Emmanuel Macron delivered a hung parliament and a historic number of seats for the far-right National Rally party.\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3663, \"end\": 3678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3756, \"end\": 3770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Paris Games offered the capital and the entire country more than two weeks of fervour and happiness that were so unexpected and appreciated given that they came after a political period dominated by the sad passions of decline and xenophobia,\\\" said an editorial in Le Monde newspaper.\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 4068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4049, \"end\": 4057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Monde\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For 17 days the stereotype of the indifferent, grumpy Frenchman went missing,\\\" wrote sports writer Owen Slot in The Times newspaper, adding that Paris had \\\"made the Olympic Games look more beautiful than ever before.\\\"\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4170, \"end\": 4179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Owen_Slot\", \"score\": 0.9999870806357289, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Owen Slot\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Owen_Slot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Owen_Slot\"}, {\"begin\": 4183, \"end\": 4192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"score\": 0.999999999577085, \"rank\": 4.232760644644753e-10, \"text\": \"The Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 4216, \"end\": 4221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.594330107958015e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing spectacle marked the beginning of the four-year countdown to the LA Games, and American gymnastics icon Simone Biles joined Los Angeles mayor Karen Bass as the Olympic flag was formally handed over.\", \"from\": 4290, \"to\": 4500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4381, \"end\": 4389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999834472, \"rank\": 1.226801042971796e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4406, \"end\": 4418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 4426, \"end\": 4437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.285574546690083e-14, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 4444, \"end\": 4454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:SA's Olympic medal hopes ratcheting up  The ceremony followed 17 days of drama-filled sporting action lit up by Biles, American sprinter Noah Lyles, Pakistan's javelin king Arshad Nadeem and casual Turkish shooter Yusuf Dikec, who has become an Internet sensation.\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4512, \"end\": 4514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999992701926138, \"rank\": 7.298072097396993e-07, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 4661, \"end\": 4669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999